    <text>
        <body>
            <head>148. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (<persName corresp="rec6rjfFsKmuW0bbp">Poindexter</persName>) to President
                    <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d148fn1">Source: <orgName
                        corresp="recft7WGb7Fww0wma">National Security Council</orgName>, National
                    Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR 093, NSDD 232. Secret. Sent for
                    action. Prepared by <persName corresp="recwQ7GkdUfKar7pC">Brooks</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="rec3WaAgwEDeqcFLV">Linhard</persName>. Copied to
                        <persName corresp="recjlYSNpDHCqlk6w">Bush</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="recnIb7zTocHk4sWn">Regan</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> wrote his initials in the
                    upper right-hand corner.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1986-08-15"
                        >August 15, 1986</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Preparations for Next <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and
                        Space Talks</rs> (<gloss target="#t_NST_1">NST</gloss>) Negotiating
                    Round</item>
            </list>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
            <p>To provide guidance for preparing for the next round of the <rs type="event"
                    corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">Nuclear and Space Talks</rs> (<gloss
                    target="#t_NST_1">NST</gloss>) in Geneva.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Facts</p>
            <p>
                <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss> negotiations resume on 18 September. The United States will be expected to
                amplify on the proposals outlined in your recent letter to <persName
                    corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName>.<note n="2" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d148fn2">Reference is to <ref target="#d138">Document 138</ref>.</note>
                To preserve confidentiality, we have not distributed the letter to the agencies. In
                order to ensure adequate preparations for the <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                </gloss> talks, therefore, separate guidance from you is needed.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
            <p>The attached draft guidance NSDD draws on your letter to General Secretary <persName
                    corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName> and on the guidance for further
                development of <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recFUg0jqFk2tUZ15">nuclear
                    testing</rs> alternatives contained in NSDD–233<note n="3" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d148fn3">NSDD 233, “Consultations on a Response to General Secretary
                        <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName>,” which <persName
                        corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> signed on July 31, was mainly
                    comprised of the draft text for the arms control portion of <persName
                        corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>’s July 25 letter to <persName
                        corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">Gorbachev</persName> (see <ref target="#d138"
                        >Document 138</ref>). The NSDD also called for two studies on testing to be
                    completed by August 15. (<persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>
                    Library, Executive Secretariat: National Security Council, National Security
                    Directive Decisions, NSDD 233)</note> (which was never <pb facs="0634" n="607"
                    xml:id="pg_607"/> distributed since it essentially contains the letter’s text).
                To ensure a coordinated approach, the NSDD also provides guidance to ensure you are
                informed in advance before any actual breach of <rs type="compound-subject"
                    corresp="reck9WPbZoOCgof6t">
                    <gloss target="#t_SALT_1">
                        <rs corresp="rec6OIA4luUvtBKNn" type="event">SALT</rs>
                    </gloss> II</rs> limits occurs.</p>
            <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
            <table cols="3">
                <row>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">OK</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">No</hi>
                    </cell>
                    <cell/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>That you sign the NSDD providing guidance for preparing for the next
                            <gloss target="#t_NST_1">
                            <rs type="event" corresp="recdBCWoByS1vPFiZ">NST</rs>
                        </gloss> negotiating session.<note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d148fn4">
                            <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName> initialed his
                            approval. The NSDD is printed as <ref target="#d149">Document
                            149</ref>.</note>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </table>
        </body>
    </text>
